PC.description: Calibration and debug tool reading the BMS firmware revision and the single cell voltages and temperatures.

HVB_noCntRoll_VCU.description: Rolling Counter; Generated by BMS and sent to VCU

HVB_noCrc8ReqMsg_VCU.description: SAE J1850 CRC8 (poly: 0x1D, initial value: 0xFF, final XOR: 0xFF) calculated using the previous message bytes.

HVB_ChargeCurLimits.description: Maximum potential charging power limit. even in case of a protection this values is shown what might possible if no protection is on

HVB_DischargeCurLimits.description: Maximum discharging power limit. even in case of a protection this values is shown what might possible if no protection is on

HVB_pwrHvb.description: instantaneous net power (+ for input, - for output)

HVB_iHvb.description: Pack Current. Negative is discharging and positive is charging pack. Source is the current sensor.

HVB_uBus.description: Battery Pack Voltage. Source is the sum of all cell voltages.

HVB_uHvb.description: Battery Pack Voltage. Source is the sum of all cell voltages.

HVB_rSoCHvb_uCellMax.description: Estimated state of charge based on the cell array with the highest OCV

HVB_rSoCHvb_uCellMin.description: Estimated state of charge based on the cell array with the lowest OCV

HVB_tCellMean.description: Average temperature of the cell bodies.

HVB_idxCell_uMax.description: Cell ID reporting the highest voltage

HVB_idxCell_uMin.description: Cell ID reporting the lowest voltage

VCU_bAllVTReq.description: Enables pack all V & T message.

VCU_bHvbInvReq.description: requested closing Inverter conductors  by VCU

INFO_01_DbgV.description: Single cell voltage (multiplexed). Sent only if enabled within BMS_00_Req.

INFO_02_DbgT.description: Single thermistor temperature (multiplexed). Sent only if enabled within BMS_00_Req.
